There is a help modal that can be opened by pressing '?' on the keyboard. The help modal is a bubble modal with a bubble text input field and a bubble list. The list is the help commands/descriptions and the text input field is the search bar for the help commands/descriptions.

there should be a flag --config for the lfm.toml path. Colors should use hex colors e.g '#000000'
lfm.toml file should have the following sections for user customization for app behavior and UI: colors, keyboard shortcuts, app behavior, and UI.



default keyboard shortcuts:
? - open help modal
ctrl+c -  quit
ctrl+q -  quit
ctl+h  -  resize panel left
ctl+l  -  resize panel right
ctl+left   - resize panel left
ctl+right -  resize panel right
up - go up a parent directory
down - go down a child directory
left - go to previous directory
right - go to next directory
home - go to home directory
end - go to root directory
enter -  opens file or directory
space - opens file or directory
